One of the Judges of The Nigerian Idol season 7, Singer Simi has explained why she has been absent for two weeks from the show. The mother of one made this known in a recent tweet.   Mr Macaroni: stop asking when I’ll get married     Victor Okhai is head judge for 8th AMVCAs     Adesua Wellington reveals oldest friendship   She noted she decided to take a break from the show because she was not feeling well, adding that she would be back soon. “I’ll be back boo. I wasn’t feeling good and the auditions are not live recordings. Pls enjoy the guest judges in the meantime,” she tweeted.